==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prefix
<hw>Pre*fix"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Prefixed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Prefixing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>praefixus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>praefigere</ets> to fix or fasten
before; <ets>prae</ets> before + <ets>figere</ets> to fix: cf. F.
<ets>pr</ets>⟦eacute⟧<ets>fix</ets> fixed beforehand, determined,
<ets>pr</ets>⟦eacute⟧<ets>fixer</ets> to prefix. See Fix.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To put or fix before, or at the beginning of,
another thing; <as>as, to <ex>prefix</ex> a syllable to a word, or a
condition to an agreement</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To set or appoint beforehand; to settle or establish
antecedently.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧ <xex>Prefixed</xex>
bounds. ⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Locke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And now he hath to her <qex>prefixt</qex> a day.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prefix</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Prefix
<hw>Pre"fix</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>pr</ets>⟦eacute⟧<ets>fixe</ets>.]</ety> <def>That which is
prefixed; esp., one or more letters or syllables combined or united with
the beginning of a word to modify its signification; <as>as,
<ex>pre-</ex> in <ex>pre</ex>fix, <ex>con-</ex> in
<ex>con</ex>jure</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prefixion</ent>⟦br⟧
